              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Native advertising is paid placement that generates immediate traffic but stops when the campaign ends. Content marketing is organic distribution through owned channels that builds gradually and runs indefinitely. The two work best in combination — native advertising amplifies content marketing assets to audiences who would never discover them organically.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

